        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 21 at 12:44PM EDT by NWS Wilmington NC</headline>
        <description>At 1244 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Longs, or near Little River, moving northeast at 5
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Iredell, Wampee, Longs, Hammond, Brooksville, Hand, and Barefoot
Landing Area Of North Myrtle Beach.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
